The '''Caribou Mother''' is an [[Inuit mythology|Inuit deity]] who represents the source of [[caribou]], formerly a vital food source for the [[Inuit|Inuit people]]. She is seen as gigantic, with people and caribou as [[lice]] on her enormous body. The Caribous Mother is known as one of the oldest Inuit Deities.

