'''Proclus''' (or '''Proklos''') '''Mallotes''' ({{lang-el|Πρόκλος Μαλλώτης}}) was a [[Stoicism|Stoic]] philosopher and a native of [[Mallus (city)|Mallus]] in [[Cilicia]]. According to the ''[[Suda]]'' he was the author of the following books:<ref>Suda, ''Proklos'' π 2470</ref>
* ''Commentary on the [[Sophisms]] of [[Diogenes of Sinope|Diogenes]]'' ({{lang-el|Ὑπόμνημα τῶν Διογένους σοφισμάτων}}) * A treatise against [[Epicurus]] ({{lang-el|Πρὸς Ἐπίκουρον}})
His date is unknown; he probably lived at some point between the 1st century BCE and the 3rd century CE. It is probably this Proclus who is mentioned by [[Proclus|Proclus Diadochus]].<ref>Proclus, ''in Timaeus'', 166</ref>
